'''鄭一嫂'''（{{bd|1775年||1844年||catIdx=Z}}）<ref name="Murray1987">{{cite book|author=Dian H. Murray|title=''Pirates of the South China Coast, 1790-1810''| url=http://books.google.com/books?id=DhSrAAAAIAAJ|date=1987年|publisher=[[史丹福大學出版社|史丹福大學出版社]]|isbn=978-0-8047-1376-4}}</ref>{{rp|64}}，原名'''石陽'''，乳名'''香姑'''，又稱'''鄭石氏'''，[[清朝|清朝]]著名女[[海盜|海盜]]。鄭一嫂本是[[妓女|妓女]]<ref name="Murray1987"/>{{rp|65}}，可能是[[蜑家|蜑家]]出身，嫁給[[鄭一|鄭一]]後成為[[海盜|海盜]]，世人遂稱她為「鄭一嫂」。鄭一死後改嫁其[[義子|義子]][[張保仔|張保仔]]，並接掌亡夫留下的紅旗幫海盜集團<ref name="袁永綸">{{Cite book |author=袁永綸 |others=蕭國健、卜永堅箋註 |title=《靖海氛記》上卷 |url=http://nansha.schina.ust.hk/Article_DB/sites/default/files/pubs/news-046.02.pdf |format=PDF |access-date=2016-09-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303182251/http://nansha.schina.ust.hk/Article_DB/sites/default/files/pubs/news-046.02.pdf |archive-date=2016-03-03 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。她在西方得到的關注比在中國多<ref name="Pennell2001">{{cite book|author=C.R. Pennell|title=Bandits at Sea: A Pirates Reader|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=i6QUCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA261|date=1 April 2001|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=978-0-8147-6679-8|page=261}}</ref>。

== 早年生涯 ==
鄭一嫂本名叫石香姑，1775年出生於[[广东省|广东省]]。她原本是在一個[[廣州市|廣州市]]的小型妓院的[[廣府人|廣府人]]<ref name="BDCW"/>，但後來被海盜擄走。在1801年，她嫁給了一位惡名昭彰的海盜[[鄭一|鄭一]]，並因此以「鄭一嫂」之名流傳後世。

== 嫁給鄭一 ==
鄭一來自一個成功的海盜家族，其從事海盜活動的紀錄最早可追溯至[[十七世紀|十七世紀]]中葉。他在繼承了[[族兄|族兄]][[鄭七|鄭七]]的事業後開始成為海盜。在娶了石陽這位「全然投入丈夫海盜事業」<ref name="Murray1987"/>{{rp|71}}的妻子之後，鄭一利用了其武裝力量及家族威望，恩威並施下使原本與他互相競爭的廣東海盜們締結統一聯盟。到了1804年，此聯盟已成為全[[中國|中國]]最強大海盜艦隊，人稱「紅旗幫」<ref name="Murray1987"/>{{rp|71}}。

== 取得領導地位 ==
1807年11月16日，鄭一在[[越南|越南]]過世<ref name="袁永綸"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2007/LIVING/worklife/08/27/woman.pirate/index.html|title=Most successful pirate was beautiful and tough -|accessdate=2018-05-07|author=|date=2007-08-28|last=Koerth|first=By  Maggie|publisher=CNN.com|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421050701/http://edition.cnn.com/2007/LIVING/worklife/08/27/woman.pirate/index.html|archive-date=2018-04-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。鄭一嫂馬上開始爭取他原本的領導地位。她開始培養自己的個人關係來讓原本敵對的海盜們認同其社會地位、穩固其威望。為了要避免與對手開始公開的鬥爭，她開始尋求其丈夫家族中最有力量的成員之支持：鄭一的姪子。
<!--She started to cultivate personal relationships to get rivals to recognize her status and solidify her authority. In order to stop her rivals before open conflict erupted, she sought the support of the most powerful members of her husband's family: his nephew Cheng Pao-yang and his cousin's son Cheng Ch'i. Then she drew on the coalition formed by her husband by building upon some of the fleet captains' existing loyalties to her husband and making herself essential to the remaining captains.<ref name=Murray/>{{rp|71}}

Since Ching Shih would have such a large force at her command, she knew she needed someone to assist her in managing the Red Flag Fleet's day-to-day operations, but remain loyal to her and be accepted by the low-level pirates. She believed there was only one man for the job, Cheung Po Tsai.<ref name=Murray/>{{rp|71}}

==Relationship with Cheung Po Tsai==
[[張保仔|張保仔]] was the son of a fisherman and had been {{tsl|en|Impressment||impressed into piracy}} at age 15, when he was captured by Cheng I, and he and Ching Shih became lovers.<ref>Konstam, Dr. Angus, ''The History of Pirates''</ref> Cheung rose rapidly through the ranks and was eventually adopted by Cheng I to give him the Rights of a son and heir.<ref name="ReferenceB">Lu K'un, Ch'eng, ''Kwang-tung hai-fang hui-lan (An Examination of Kwangtung's Sea Defense)''</ref>

As soon as Ching Shih chose Cheung, she acted quickly to solidify the partnership with intimacy. The two became lovers within weeks and eventually married.<ref name="ReferenceB"/> Ching Shih gave birth to Cheung's son sometime between the ages of 32 and 35. Cheung Po Tsai died at 36, causes unknown.-->

